<Collection><ShortName>c4dmtp</ShortName><VersionId>1</VersionId><InsertTime>2002-05-29T00:00:00.000Z</InsertTime><LastUpdate>2011-07-07T14:04:17.000Z</LastUpdate><LongName>CAMEX-4 DC-8 MICROWAVE TEMPERATURE PROFILER (MTP)</LongName><DataSetId>CAMEX-4 DC-8 MICROWAVE TEMPERATURE PROFILER (MTP) V1</DataSetId><Description>The Microwave Temperature Profiler (MTP) is a passive microwave radiometer which measures the thermal emmission from oxygen molecules in the atmosphere for a selection of elevation angles. Current observing frequencies are 56.6 and 58.8 GHz. Measured brightness temperatues versus elevation angle is converted to air temperature versus altitude using a statistical retrieval procedure. An altitude temperature profile is produced every three km along the flight path.</Description><Orderable>false</Orderable><Visible>true</Visible><ProcessingLevelId>1B</ProcessingLevelId><ArchiveCenter>GHRC</ArchiveCenter><Price>0</Price><SpatialKeywords><Keyword>ATLANTIC OCEAN</Keyword></SpatialKeywords><TemporalKeywords><Keyword>DAILY</Keyword></TemporalKeywords><Temporal><RangeDateTime><BeginningDateTime>2001-08-15T00:00:00.000Z</BeginningDateTime><EndingDateTime>2001-09-26T23:59:00.000Z</EndingDateTime></RangeDateTime></Temporal><Contacts><Contact><Role>GHRC USER SERVICES</Role><OrganizationAddresses /><OrganizationPhones /><OrganizationEmails><Email>ghrc-dmg@itsc.uah.edu</Email></OrganizationEmails><ContactPersons /></Contact></Contacts><ScienceKeywords><ScienceKeyword><CategoryKeyword>EARTH SCIENCE</CategoryKeyword><TopicKeyword>ATMOSPHERE</TopicKeyword><TermKeyword>ATMOSPHERIC TEMPERATURE</TermKeyword><VariableLevel1Keyword><Value>TEMPERATURE PROFILES</Value></VariableLevel1Keyword></ScienceKeyword></ScienceKeywords><Platforms><Platform><ShortName>NASA DC-8</ShortName><LongName>NASA DC-8</LongName><Type>AIRCRAFT</Type><Characteristics /><Instruments><Instrument><ShortName>MICROWAVE TEMPERATURE PROFILER</ShortName><Characteristics /><Sensors><Sensor><ShortName>MICROW